e total category with 146-166-312.\", \"from\": 2581, \"to\": 2748, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2605, \"end\": 2607, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithium\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 6.820197953480685e-13, \"text\": \"Li\", \"types\": [\"Q11173\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithium\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a striking contrast\", \"from\": 2584, \"to\": 2603}, {\"ngram\": \"an exceptional performance\", \"from\": 2618, \"to\": 2644}, {\"ngram\": \"his own snatch world record\", \"from\": 2657, \"to\": 2684}, {\"ngram\": \"the total category\", \"from\": 2712, \"to\": 2730}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But it was Hampton Morris who stole the spotlight as the unexpected dark horse, stunning the crowd with a monumental final lift that not only shattered Li's clean and jerk world record but also made him the first American man in 55 years to achieve a senior-level world record.\", \"from\": 2749, \"to\": 3026, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2760, \"end\": 2767, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Hampton\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0866333289611676e-16, \"text\": \"Hampton\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Hampton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Hampton\"}, {\"begin\": 2768, \"end\": 2774, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benny_Morris\", \"score\": 0.9053133508858353, \"rank\": 0.10458991232378091, \"text\": \"Morris\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benny_Morris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benny_Morris\"}, {\"begin\": 2901, \"end\": 2903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithium\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 6.820197953480685e-13, \"text\": \"Li\", \"types\": [\"Q11173\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbp